The paper deals with the problem of reducing delay in downloading data from cloud storage systems, which involves information theory (IT) and distributed computing (DC) concepts. The model involves multiple servers and a queue, which falls under the networked and internet-based systems (NI) category. The paper also discusses work-conserving and greedy scheduling schemes, which are related to control and optimization in systems (SY) and performance analysis and optimization (PF).
